The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 21: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh will be briefed on the economic outlook in the backdrop of high inflation by his economic advisory council on Friday. C. Rangarajan, chairman of the Prime Ministers economic advisory council, is expected to brief the Prime Minister about the GDP projections and the challenges before the economy ahead of the monetary policy review by the Reserve Bank.                            
	 New Delhi, July 21: The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India today informed the Supreme Court that it planned to cap the monthly charges of cable television at Rs 250 across the country, except for pockets where a conditional access system was implemented.                            
	 Calcutta, July 21: The United Bank of India has handed over Rs 53.29 crore as the final dividend for 2009-10 as part of the President of Indias shareholding of 84.20 per cent in the bank to finance minister Pranab Mukherjee.                             
	 London, July 21: Consumer goods group Reckitt Benckiser is to buy Durex condoms and Scholl sandals maker SSL for an agreed 2.5 billion ($3.8 billion) to increase its presence in health and personal care.                            
	 San Francisco, July 21: Apple Inc has announced an upbeat revenue forecast that trounced Wall Streets expectations and eased fears that the Antennagate controversy around its iPhone 4s reception would hurt sales.                                                                                                                          
